Current component signature (lines 9-14):
  export const CodeBlock = ({
    className,
    children,
    'data-language': language,
    ...props
  }: HTMLAttributes<HTMLPreElement> & { 'data-language'?: string }) => {

Add data-nocopy extraction:
  export const CodeBlock = ({
    className,
    children,
    'data-language': language,
    'data-nocopy': nocopy,
    ...props
  }: HTMLAttributes<HTMLPreElement> & { 'data-language'?: string; 'data-nocopy'?: string }) => {

Then conditionally render the copy UI:
  const showCopy = nocopy === undefined;

  return (
    <div className="relative my-6">
      {showCopy && (
        <div className="bg-code-bg hidden items-center ...">
          ...
        </div>
      )}
      <pre
        className={cn('bg-code-bg text-code-fg overflow-x-auto rounded-(--radius) p-4', showCopy && 'md:rounded-t-none', className)}
        ...
      >
        <span ref={preRef}>{children}</span>
      </pre>
      {showCopy && (
        <Button ... className="absolute top-3 right-3 md:hidden">
          ...
        </Button>
      )}
    </div>
  );

The data-nocopy attribute will be passed through from rehype-pretty-code's meta string processing. rehype-pretty-code passes unrecognized meta key-value pairs as data attributes on the <pre> element. So a code fence written as:

  ```text nocopy
  [tsc] Found 0 errors.
  ```

will result in rehype-pretty-code setting data-nocopy on the <pre> element, which flows to CodeBlock via MDX.tsx's pre: CodeBlock mapping.

However, this only works if rehype-pretty-code is configured to pass meta strings through. Check the rehype-pretty-code docs — in v0.14.x, meta strings are automatically parsed and set as data attributes on the <pre> element by default. The key 'nocopy' in the meta string becomes data-nocopy on the pre element.

If rehype-pretty-code does NOT automatically pass meta strings as data attributes, an alternative approach is needed: configure a filterMetaString or transformerMetaString option in content-collections.ts to ensure meta keys are preserved as data attributes. But try the simple approach first — it likely works out of the box.
